description:
&lt;p&gt;East Sussex Healthcare NHS Trust are recruiting a general paediatrician to join our dynamic multidisciplinary team. The department is on a journey to ensure we achieve the best outcomes for children as part of the local integrated healthcare system.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role would suit a newly qualified consultant as it requires considerable hands on acute paediatrics working in the short stay unit and emergency department. The successful candidate will already have or be committed to developing a sub speciality interest complementary to the needs of the department. The successful candidate will be supported to complete SPIN training if required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is the opportunity to apply for a honory contract with Brighton and Sussex Medical School for the development of an interest in Medical Education. The department would also consider a joint appointment with a tertiary centre to enable the successful candidate to continue subspecialty or academic work.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date to be confirmed&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Dr Matthew Clark, Speciality Lead 07916350488 or Dr Melanie Liebenberg, Chief of Division on 07703815572.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
